The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and cross-modal networks (X-CNNs) for image and data processing, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a data-driven approach for learning the topology of X-CNNs, which involves optimization and learning procedures, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the implementation of the methodology in the Xsertion library, which suggests a potential connection to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
